c/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/GeneralUtils.java:56:     * Captures output and throws a RuntimeException if the exit code is non-zero.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/GeneralUtils.java:83:            throw new RuntimeException(errorMessage + \". See output:\\n\" + execOutput.toString(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/ArtifactMetadataDiscoveryUtils.java:15:import java.io.IOException;\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/ArtifactMetadataDiscoveryUtils.java:36:    public static void initializeDiscoveryFile(Path discoveryFile, String coordinates) throws IOException {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/ArtifactMetadataDiscoveryUtils.java:55:    public static void writeDiscoveryFile(Path discoveryFile, DiscoveredArtifactMetadata metadata) throws IOException {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/ArtifactMetadataDiscoveryUtils.java:64:    public static DiscoveredArtifactMetadata readDiscoveryFile(Path discoveryFile) throws IOException {\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes a native-image runtime failure for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the runtime/native fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair metadata or tests after an existing library version compiles and builds a native image, but the native image fails when the test runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library is already supported, so the goal is to restore native-image behavior for a newer version while preserving existing dynamic-access coverage.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:50:   - Test changes are acceptable when the upstream API or runtime behavior changed, but they must still exercise the native path that previously failed.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:53:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:55:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - If metadata fixes make the native run pass but the dynamic-access ratio drops, ask for restored coverage first. Passing native execution is not enough by itself.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:76:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:84:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API surface.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:90:- The fix makes native execution pass by skipping the failing native path, disabling assertions, or removing coverage.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:91:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fi