d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair test sources or test dependencies after an existing library is bumped and the new version no longer compiles with the old test code. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to preserve working coverage across the version update rather than prove a brand-new metadata contribution from scratch.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:17:- Be more relaxed than `library-new-request`: do not reject only because a test resembles older coverage, stays in an existing package layout, or contains compatibility branches for multiple supported versions.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:18:- Do not accept changes that remove meaningful test coverage just to make `javac` pass.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:21:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:54:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:74:   - Prefer seeing the full target `test` lane green because a compile fix can still reduce runtime or native coverage.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:76:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:84:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API surface.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:90:- The fix makes compilation pass by weakening or bypassing the test instead of adapting it to the changed API while preserving meaningful coverage.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2278-d56b4a74/skills/